OL,3,CDressage competitors grow concerned
OL,4,Cover the sport's future
OL,6,FGuernsey dressage competitors and
OL,7,Fjudges have shared their concerns over
OL,8,Fthe future of the equestrian sport on
OL,9,Fthe island.
OL,11,FMaxime Whalley is one of Guernsey's
OL,12,Fbest dressage riders and is one step
OL,13,Faway from reaching the Grand Prix
OL,14,Fcompetition - the highest level in the
OL,15,Fsport.
OL,17,FHowever, she is fearful about the
OL,18,Fequestrian sport's presence on the
OL,19,Fisland.
